Updates to the Return to School plan and Calendar were released today.

Banner School Boards Approved Plan:
Highlights of the School Board's adopted plan for this school year that occurred during today's meeting are as follows:

The School start date for all Banner students (traditional and virtual students) will be August 19th.

Back to school times are August 10th and 11th by appointment only with each teacher in order to bring your student's supplies and meet their teacher.

Virtual Learning days for all students are August 21st, 28th, September 11th, 18th and 25th. Students will not be physically attending school on those days, but are responsible for the lessons/assignments and due dates…

post_text:
Banner School Distant Virtual Learning

Parent Guide

This is a very challenging time for our nation. The staff at Banner is here to help as our resources allow. The goal for the remainder of this school year is to maintain the health and safety of our school community and provide additional resources for our students to learn at home. United in kindness to others is the greatest gift we can give each other. If your family is struggling for basic necessities, please reach out to me (mprior@banner.k12.ok.us). I will do all I can to help! We will overcome this crisis as a School, a Community, a State, and as the United States of America.
Mr. Prior – Banner Superintendent

OVERVIEW & PURPOSE…

post_text:
Banner's Parent Guide for Distant Learning
April 02, 2020

From the desk of the Superintendent

To our Banner School Community, we have posted a Parent Guide to distant learning to communicate and answer upcoming questions. We have included all contact information for certified staff. We are scheduling days and times for parents to drive up and pick up student items and return library books and uniforms. We will have all student items bagged up and labeled. The days and times are April 7 from 7 am to 10 am and April 8 from 1pm-4pm. All parents will remain in their cars much like the parent pick up process. Please refer to the information we have posted in the Parent Guide. Your families' health and wellbeing is very important to us and we are here to help as much as possible. Thank you for your cooperation in this challenging time, Mr. Prior

post_text:
From Banner School:
Our resource officer, Deputy Glenn Cowart of the Canadian County Sheriff's Department, just suffered a massive fire to his home where he lost everything, including his three dogs. He and his wife managed to escape the fire without harm. Miss Laura has started to collect gas cards and visa gift cards to give to Deputy Glenn to help them through this tragedy. If you would like to donate, please send a gift card to the office, or a check made out to Glenn Cowart. All donations are appreciated. We will be handing over all that has been collected on Friday, November 22. Thank you in advance for recognizing his service to our school and community and pouring out blessings on him this Thanksgiving.
Thank you.
